{
  "texts": [
    "There has been one recent publication on DrugGPT along the lines of ChatGPT.",
    "This is covered in more detail later in this article.",
    "In the case of AI-driven drug discovery, GAI may be divided into three classes based on how they are used to generate novel compounds:",
    "• Distribution-learning (Brown et al., 2019): The system produces new molecules to fill the same chemical space as the training set.",
    "Algorithms for learning distributions are typically judged based on how well they reproduce the characteristics of the training set, with metrics like the Kullback-Leibler (Kullback and Leibler, 1951), (KL) divergence (used, for example, to analyze the distribution of calculated physicochemical features of the molecules) or the Fre'chet ChemNet Distance (Preuer et al., 2018) (FCD), used to quantify structural and functional similarity."
  ]
}